metadata.dc:description: Authors present a case of anencephaly with trisomy 18, diagnosed prenatally by altrasonographic screening and culture of amniotic cells. This association is rare in newborn children. They discuss if this is due to a high prenatal letality or a random event.
metadata.dc:title: Diagnóstico prenatal en un feto con anencefalia y trisomía 18.
[Prenatal diagnosis in a fetus with anencephaly and trisomy 18].
